III. Equation Solving
There are two types of solvers used in the FEA for solving the linear systems of algebraic equations, mainly, the direct methods and iterative methods.
Direct Methods (Gauss Elimination): โข Solution time proportional to NB2 (with N being the dimension of the matrix, B the bandwidth of the FEA systems) โข Suitable for small to medium problems (with DOFs in the 100,000 range), or slender structures (small bandwidth) โข Easy to handle multiple load cases

Iterative Methods: โข Solution time is unknown beforehand โข Reduced storage requirement โข Suitable for large problems, or bulky structures (large bandwidth, converge faster) โข Need to solve the system again for different load cases

